[Our thanks to Sabine Zentis and Tamas Torok for this report of a case of tularemia initially diagnosed as anthrax. Why they suspected "anthrax" is hard to determine other than his "boils". Interesting that the subsequent health of his dog after eating the muskrat is not mentioned. Dogs are susceptible to this pathogen. Maybe he cooked the muskrat before feeding it to his dog. Or maybe his physician forgot to ask.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/3PZ4. To find Krasnoyarsk in Siberia, go to http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krasnoyarsk. - Mod.MHJ]
